-- India to Play Pakistan in Cricket’s Champions Trophy Next Year
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-08-21T12:19:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-21/india-to-play-pakistan-in-cricket-s-champions-trophy-next-year.html
India will play arch-rival  Pakistan 
in the group stage of cricket’s Champions Trophy in England and
 Wales  next year.  South Africa  meets India in the opening game on June 6, and
defending champion Australia’s first match is against England
two days later.  It’s the last time the 50-over event will be held. It
features the top eight teams in the International Cricket
Council one-day rankings in two groups of four. The first two in
each group advance to the semifinals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty in London at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 